## 1. Scope
### 1.1 In Scope
- Authenticated users can upload high-resolution images to their profile gallery
- Upload interface is only available to users with an active session
- Uploads are processed through a secure API Gateway
- Server-side optimization and compression of images
- Synchronous, inline virus scanning and file validation for each upload
- Validated images are stored in AWS S3
- Uploaded images sync instantly to the user's public portfolio grid
- Single-file image uploads (PNG, JPEG)
- Authentication and session validation for upload access
- API Gateway upload endpoint
- Server-side image optimization and compression
- Inline virus scanning and file validation
- AWS S3 storage integration
- Real-time grid update and rendering

### 1.2 Out of Scope
- Client-side image optimization or pre-processing
- Support for non-image or alternative formats (WebP, GIF, SVG, TIFF)
- Batch or multi-file uploads
- Storage solutions other than AWS S3

#### 3.2.2 Out of Scope
