## 2. Test Approach
### 2.1 Testing Levels
- UI / Front-End Component Level (Upload button visibility, grid rendering)
- API Gateway / Backend Endpoint Level (Upload request validation, file processing, virus scanning)
- Integration Level (AWS S3 storage, real-time grid update propagation)
- End-to-End System Level (Full upload-to-render workflow under network constraints)

### 2.2 Testing Types
- Functional Testing
- Boundary Value & Negative Testing (File size, authentication, mime-type enforcement)
- Security Testing (Header/magic number validation, session enforcement)
- Performance & SLA Latency Testing (2.5s upload-to-render on 4G network)
- Integration Testing (S3 storage, grid update propagation)

### 2.3 Test Design Techniques
- Boundary Value Analysis (File size acceptance at 10.00MB, rejection at 10.01MB and above)
- Equivalence Partitioning (Valid vs. invalid authentication/session states, supported vs. unsupported file types)
- State Transition Testing (Session expiration, upload button enable/disable, grid update states)
- Negative Testing (Spoofed file extensions, unauthenticated upload attempts, unsupported formats)
- Performance Profiling (Network throttling to 4G, measuring end-to-end latency)

### 2.4 Environments Needed
- Staging environment with user authentication and session management enabled
- API Gateway endpoint with backend virus scanning and file validation microservices
- AWS S3 test bucket with isolated access for upload validation
- Mock services for simulating expired/invalid sessions and malicious file payloads
- Network shaping tools to enforce 4G mobile bandwidth constraints
- Test data matrix: PNG/JPEG files at 9.99MB, 10.00MB, 10.01MB, and files with spoofed headers
- Automated UI test harness for real-time grid rendering verification

### 2.5 Approach Description
This test approach implements a multi-layered validation strategy targeting all in-scope acceptance criteria.
UI-level tests will verify upload button gating based on session state and confirm real-time grid updates post-upload without manual refresh.
API and backend tests will enforce strict file size and mime-type boundaries using Boundary Value Analysis and Equivalence Partitioning, including negative scenarios for spoofed headers and unauthorized access.
Security validation will focus on session enforcement and backend header inspection.
Performance tests will throttle network conditions to standard 4G and measure the complete upload-to-render loop, ensuring SLA compliance within 2.5 seconds.
All scenarios will be executed in a staging environment with isolated AWS S3 buckets and mock services for session and payload manipulation, ensuring robust coverage of both positive and negative paths.

## 3. Quality Objectives
- Verify upload button visibility for authenticated sessions only
- Validate rejection of uploads from unauthenticated or expired sessions
- Test acceptance of PNG and JPEG files up to 10MB
- Ensure files >=10.01MB are rejected with a clear validation message
- Confirm backend rejects files with spoofed extensions
- Measure total upload-to-render time does not exceed 2.5 seconds on 4G
- Check that uploaded images appear instantly on the public portfolio grid without manual refresh

