## 6. Test Schedule / Milestone
- Test script development: 3 days
- Environment setup and data seeding: 2 days
- Automated and manual test execution: 4 days
- Performance and security validation: 2 days
- Results analysis and reporting: 2 days
**Total Estimated Duration:** 13 days
**Core Resources:** 1 QA Automation Engineer, 1 Manual QA, 1 DevOps/Infra support

## 7. Assumptions
- Test environments and AWS S3 buckets are provisioned and accessible
- All required test data (valid/invalid images, spoofed files) is available
- Automation frameworks (Playwright, PyTest, JMeter, tcconfig, OWASP ZAP) are licensed and installed
- Team members have access to necessary credentials and permissions
- Upstream authentication and session management services are stable

## 9. Risk Mitigation Table
Risk Description | Impact | Likelihood | Severity | Mitigation Action
---|---|---|---|---
Dynamic session expiration or token invalidation during upload | Medium | Medium | High | Implement session keep-alive checks and retry logic in automation scripts
SLA breach due to backend virus scan latency | High | Medium | High | Profile and optimize virus scan microservice, run load tests with JMeter
Network throttling tool (tcconfig) misconfiguration | Medium | Low | Medium | Validate network shaping setup before test execution, maintain baseline logs
AWS S3 permission or bucket misalignment | High | Low | High | Pre-validate S3 IAM roles and bucket policies in staging
False positives in file header validation (magic number check) | Low | Medium | Medium | Maintain a test matrix of valid/invalid files, review backend validation logic

